{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018TqoDXpUiX3fYm8T1CP9e6","type":"tool_result","content":"=== stage_01 ===\nA 3-node MongoDB replica set is not deployed in the mongodb namespace.\n\nTask:\n- Deploy a 3-member replica set with authentication enabled. Back it with a\n  StatefulSet named `mongodb-replica` (pods `mongodb-replica-0..2`).\n- Name the replica set itself `mongodb-replica` (the mongod `replSetName` /\n  `rs.initiate` `_id` must be exactly `mongodb-replica`, not the `rs0` default).\n- Create a headless Service named `mongodb-replica-svc` (clusterIP: None) that\n  governs the StatefulSet, so each member is reachable at its stable DNS name\n  `mongodb-replica-<n>.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`.\n- Create an admin user and an application user.\n- Ensure the replica set is healthy (PRIMARY + SECONDARY members).\n- Confirm data can be written and read from the application database.\n\nCredentials:\n- Admin user: admin-user / admin123password\n- App user: app-user / app123password\n- Store the passwords in Secrets:\n  * admin-user-password (key: password)\n  * app-user-password (key: password)\n\nNotes:\n- Use a keyfile for internal replica set authentication.\n- No operators or CRDs.\n=== stage_02 ===\nReplica set is not healthy. Restore a stable 3-member replica set without data loss.\n=== stage_03 ===\nThe MongoDB replica set has two data-bearing members and a running arbiter pod.\nElections are unstable unless you add a voting member without increasing storage cost.\n\nTask:\n- Stabilize elections without adding a data-bearing member.\n- Data in the app database must remain intact.\n=== stage_04 ===\nA 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\nScale the replica set to 5 members without data loss or loss of availability.\nDo not use operators or CRDs.\n\nNote: the replica set's member count may be actively changed by an external\nprocess during this task. Verify the current StatefulSet size against the\ntarget before assuming the cluster is healthy.\n=== stage_05 ===\nA 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace with auth enabled.\nApply the platform's updated observability and storage policy:\n- Increase logging verbosity by one level relative to the current setting.\n- Set the slow-operation threshold to 2x the current value.\n- Switch the WiredTiger journal compression to the approved standard (zlib).\n\nEnsure the changes are applied consistently across all members and data remains available.\nNo operators or CRDs.\n\nReminder: an earlier external change may have shrunk the replica set. Confirm\nthe member count matches the requested target before finishing.\n=== stage_06 ===\nA 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace with auth enabled.\nPods are repeatedly failing readiness/liveness checks even though MongoDB is healthy.\n\nTask:\n- Tune the probes so the replica set becomes stable.\n- All pods must become Ready.\n- Replica set should have 1 PRIMARY and 2 SECONDARY members.\n\nNotes:\n- Do not disable authentication.\n- No operators or CRDs.\n\nReminder: an earlier external change may have shrunk the replica set. Confirm\nthe member count matches the requested target before finishing.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"053d4746-61f3-4a42-b9e9-f3e46abc0bba","uuid":"18cb738f-afe6-48b3-a830-a7042807a999","timestamp":"2026-07-02T01:24:52.065Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== stage_01 ===\nA 3-node MongoDB replica set is not deployed in the mongodb namespace.\n\nTask:\n- Deploy a 3-member replica set with authentication enabled. Back it with a\n  StatefulSet named `mongodb-replica` (pods `mongodb-replica-0..2`).\n- Name the replica set itself `mongodb-replica` (the mongod `replSetName` /\n  `rs.initiate` `_id` must be exactly `mongodb-replica`, not the `rs0` default).\n- Create a headless Service named `mongodb-replica-svc` (clusterIP: None) that\n  governs the Stateful